<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98592662063302></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98592662063302><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=10&mid=98592662063302>RE: Tanking Or Arrows</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=10&mid=98592662063302#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 29th 11:30 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To answer one of the replies here, don't kill the wildlife! You are a ranger!&nbsp;&nbsp;When I solo, I am doing it for one of two reasons, to get archery up, or because I want to be alone, or both.  Verant made rangers to be a melee class, without making them good tanks, so you play the tank in the group, but you have to be careful.  As you go up in lvls, this weakness will make itself more and more felt.  In groups your bow is used to pull, and nothing else.  You will do more dmg in melee, and be more useful in melee than you will with your bow.  As far as equipment, get your fletching up, but your emphasis should be on your armor, the better your AC, the longer you live.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
